{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":611,"text":"I have the answer to a question that we've all asked."},{"time":4212,"text":"The question is,"},{"time":5329,"text":"Why is it that the letter X"},{"time":7613,"text":"represents the unknown?"},{"time":9611,"text":"Now I know we learned that in math class,"},{"time":12578,"text":"but now it's everywhere in the culture --"},{"time":14329,"text":"The X prize, the X-Files,"},{"time":17130,"text":"Project X, TEDx."},{"time":21053,"text":"Where'd that come from?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23048,"text":"About six years ago"},{"time":24266,"text":"I decided that I would learn Arabic,"},{"time":26982,"text":"which turns out to be a supremely logical language."},{"time":30934,"text":"To write a word or a phrase"},{"time":33251,"text":"or a sentence in Arabic"},{"time":34932,"text":"is like crafting an equation,"},{"time":37165,"text":"because every part is extremely precise"},{"time":39531,"text":"and carries a lot of information."},{"time":42383,"text":"That's one of the reasons"},{"time":43733,"text":"so much of what we've come to think of"},{"time":45248,"text":"as Western science and mathematics and engineering"},{"time":49067,"text":"was really worked out in the first few centuries of the Common Era"},{"time":52389,"text":"by the Persians and the Arabs and the Turks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55705,"text":"This includes the little system in Arabic"},{"time":58022,"text":"called al-jebra."},{"time":59738,"text":"And al-jebr roughly translates to"},{"time":62906,"text":"\"the system for reconciling disparate parts.\""},{"time":66605,"text":"Al-jebr finally came into English as algebra."},{"time":70655,"text":"One example among many."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72822,"text":"The Arabic texts containing this mathematical wisdom"},{"time":76788,"text":"finally made their way to Europe --"},{"time":78571,"text":"which is to say Spain --"},{"time":79857,"text":"in the 11th and 12th centuries."},{"time":82322,"text":"And when they arrived"},{"time":83472,"text":"there was tremendous interest"},{"time":85355,"text":"in translating this wisdom"},{"time":87089,"text":"into a European language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88738,"text":"But there were problems."},{"time":90756,"text":"One problem"},{"time":92473,"text":"is there are some sounds in Arabic"},{"time":95106,"text":"that just don't make it through a European voice box"},{"time":98105,"text":"without lots of practice."},{"time":100372,"text":"Trust me on that one."},{"time":102106,"text":"Also, those very sounds"},{"time":104323,"text":"tend not to be represented"},{"time":106237,"text":"by the characters that are available in European languages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109825,"text":"Here's one of the culprits."},{"time":111639,"text":"This is the letter SHeen,"},{"time":113523,"text":"and it makes the sound we think of as SH -- \"sh.\""},{"time":117122,"text":"It's also the very first letter"},{"time":119724,"text":"of the word shalan,"},{"time":122156,"text":"which means \"something\""},{"time":123950,"text":"just like the the English word \"something\" --"},{"time":125798,"text":"some undefined, unknown thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129084,"text":"Now in Arabic,"},{"time":130249,"text":"we can make this definite"},{"time":131450,"text":"by adding the definite article \"al.\""},{"time":133598,"text":"So this is al-shalan --"},{"time":136200,"text":"the unknown thing."},{"time":137850,"text":"And this is a word that appears throughout early mathematics,"},{"time":141153,"text":"such as this 10th century derivation of proofs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148353,"text":"The problem for the Medieval Spanish scholars"},{"time":150863,"text":"who were tasked with translating this material"},{"time":153431,"text":"is that the letter SHeen and the word shalan"},{"time":157913,"text":"can't be rendered into Spanish"},{"time":159863,"text":"because Spanish doesn't have that SH,"},{"time":162449,"text":"that \"sh\" sound."},{"time":163746,"text":"So by convention,"},{"time":165328,"text":"they created a rule in which"},{"time":166994,"text":"they borrowed the CK sound, \"ck\" sound,"},{"time":171212,"text":"from the classical Greek"},{"time":172960,"text":"in the form of the letter Kai."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175641,"text":"Later when this material was translated"},{"time":178360,"text":"into a common European language,"},{"time":180708,"text":"which is to say Latin,"},{"time":182758,"text":"they simply replaced the Greek Kai"},{"time":184791,"text":"with the Latin X."},{"time":187141,"text":"And once that happened,"},{"time":188410,"text":"once this material was in Latin,"},{"time":190875,"text":"it formed the basis for mathematics textbooks"},{"time":194458,"text":"for almost 600 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196541,"text":"But now we have the answer to our question."},{"time":198559,"text":"Why is it that X is the unknown?"},{"time":201340,"text":"X is the unknown"},{"time":203163,"text":"because you can't say \"sh\" in Spanish."},{"time":206945,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":209329,"text":"And I thought that was worth sharing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211646,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}